         <abstract id="aspace_4adfd6f98bd18f8301313c4182282c5a">A collection of autograph letters and facsimiles of which the largest number are letters to and from Daniel Webster. Also in the collection is a volume of drafts of letters, pamphlets, and speeches composed by Stephen Devalson Dillaye between 1864-1868 on current political issues. Dillaye was a Democrat who opposed radical abolitionism, but sided with the North in the Civil War.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname relator="col" source="local">
               <part>Vann, Irving Goodwin, 1842-1921</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
